verbose_text: Levels of PLAA abundance and/or function are further reduced in Plaa G23V/- compound heterozygote mice, resulting in accelerated decline with pronounced paralysis and respiratory distress (XREF_FIG A, 3B, and XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY C) and the pups die before weaning (P17-P21 [postnatal day 17-21]; XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY).
